eration of scientists professionals and citizens who approach and solve problems in a new way a systematic interdisciplinary way learn more helpful links visit us advising faq alumni spotlight news sep 07 2011 julie kennedy was promoted to professor teaching summer 2011 jun 06 2010 a tale of two atolls stanford researchers study the impact of fishing on remote coral reefs may 26 2010 op ed regrowing the farm view all news upcoming events there are currently no scheduled events view event calendar environmental art earth systems student ethan estess promotes wildlife conservation with his california brown pelican sculpture which he constructed from garbage click here to read more about ethan's environmental artwork or check out a video of his kinetic structure earth systems program yang and yamazaki environment and energy building 473 via ortega rm 131 stanford university stanford ca 94305 4215 phone 650 725 7427 fax 650 725 0958 related resources hartley conference center health and safety computers resources room resources how can we help maps & directions stanfordwho office of the registrar contact us connect to earth sciences facebook itunes u twitter youtube
